WhatsApp has become part of our daily lives and some companies now rely on it for communication. We have seen that we can now delete messages we sent by mistake but a trick has been found to retrieve those messages. If someone deletes a message they sent you, you might become curious about what was being said in that message and and want to read it and you can do that via an app called Notisave. WhatsApp backs up messages, and all you have to do is delete WhatsApp and reinstall it again. Here is a video below explaining exactly how this works, so that you can read all accidentally sent messages as a true FBI agent. 